---
/**
 * rest-api · 0008 · Figure 5 — "OWASP API #1 · Broken Object Level Authorization".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson. References the source's shared #arw and
 * #arwR arrow markers, inlined here in this figure's own <defs> with the same
 * ids/fills so the component is self-contained. See Fig1.astro for the rationale.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 178"
        role="img"
        aria-label="BOLA: an authenticated, role-permitted user changes the id in the path and the API returns another tenant's object because it skipped the ownership check"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path>
            </marker>
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">OWASP API #1 · BROKEN OBJECT LEVEL AUTHORIZATION</text
            >
            <rect x="10" y="30" width="150" height="58" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="85"
                y="51"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓ authenticated</text
            >
            <text
                x="85"
                y="68"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓ role-permitted</text
            >
            <text x="85" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >RBAC/ABAC passed</text
            >
            <line x1="160" y1="59" x2="196" y2="59" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <rect
                x="198"
                y="30"
                width="200"
                height="58"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="298"
                y="52"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">GET /accounts/{'{'}id{'}'}</text
            >
            <text x="298" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a2218"
                >attacker swaps id → 1042 → 1043</text
            >
            <text x="298" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >no ownership check</text
            >
            <line x1="398" y1="59" x2="434" y2="59" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
            <rect x="436" y="30" width="194" height="58" rx="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="533"
                y="55"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">someone else's data 💥</text
            >
            <text x="533" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a2218"
                >cross-tenant leak</text
            >
            <rect
                x="120"
                y="108"
                width="400"
                height="34"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="320"
                y="123"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a"
                >FIX: on every object access, verify the principal owns THAT exact object</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="136" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#244a2e"
                >(tenant / owner check) — non-optional</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Unguessable ids are not authorization — they're obscurity.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Two siblings round out the top: <strong>#2 Broken Authentication</strong> (weak validation, credential
        stuffing, no login rate-limit) and <strong>#3 BOPLA</strong> (reading/writing fields the caller
        shouldn't, e.g. mass-assigning <code>isAdmin</code>).<sup><a href="#s1">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
